subSubSection.paragraph:
This species is similar to 
Diptacus lonicerae
Kuang, 2001, but can be differentiated from the latter by prodorsal shield with admedian lines and submedian lines separated (admedian lines and submedian lines connected in 
Diptacus lonicerae
), prodorsal shield frontal lobe wide and broad (frontal lobe small in 
Diptacus lonicerae
), female genital coverflap with 4 longitudinal ridges in 2 ranks, 1 near the base and 3 far from the base (female genital coverflap with 6-8 longitudinal ridges in 
Diptacus lonicerae
).
